  ],
  "text": "In the Grafana to Loki query path, the HTTP client that acts as the entry point for outbound Loki queries is the LokiAPI struct located in grafana/grafana at pkg/tsdb/loki/api.go (lines 29-34). This struct wraps an http.Client and contains the following fields: client (*http.Client), url (string), log (log.Logger), and tracer (trace.Tracer). The LokiAPI.DataQuery method (line 161) executes queries against the Loki server, using makeDataRequest (line 46) to construct HTTP requests to /loki/api/v1/query for instant queries (line 86 in api.go). On the Loki server side, incoming HTTP instant query requests to the /loki/api/v1/query endpoint are parsed and handled by the InstantQueryHandler function located in grafana/loki at pkg/querier/http.go. This function validates that queries are sample expressions (metric queries rather than log queries), checks entry limits, and executes the query using the appropriate query engine. The call chain flows from Grafana's datasource service through the LokiAPI client to the Loki server's InstantQueryHandler."
}

